A 17-YEAR-OLD boy crashed his dad’s car into a stationary vehicle on Umkhonto Wesizwe Road in Waterloo, KZN at the weekend. According to a statement posted on Facebook by Reaction Unit South Africa, the teenager was returning home shortly after dropping their mother off in church. “He crashed his father’s green Mercedes-Benz into the rear of an unoccupied white Toyota Corolla. “His 13-year-old brother was in the vehicle at the time of the incident,” read the statement.  It is reported that when medics arrived at the scene, they established that both brothers were not injured. “Their father arrived on the scene and informed Reaction Officers that he had no knowledge that the teenager had been driving his vehicle,” the statement concluded.